<title>How A* Pathfinding works</title>

<h1>What is A*?</h1>
<p>A* (pronounced A Star) is an algorithm that searches for the shortest way to reach it's goal. Here is a gif showing a search in progress:<br></p1>

<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5d/Astar_progress_animation.gif" width=250 height=250>
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A*_search_algorithm">Image source</a> 

<h1>Components</h1>
<p><b>NODE</b> - Each grid where the pathfinding takes place is made up of something called nodes. Nodes are areas where the robot is allowed to go through.<br><br>


<b>G</b> - How much movement cost will it take to reach a grid, creating a path.<br>
<b>H</b> - How much movement cost will it take to reach the starting grid to the end grid.<br>
<b>F</b> - The sum of G and H<br></p>

<br></p>

